Two people have been killed in an accident in Roodepoort, Gauteng. Reports from the scene indicate that two light motor vehicles were involved in a collision.  Medics assessed the scene and found that two people had sustained fatal injuries and were sadly declared deceased on the scene.Â  Four other people sustained serious injuries and were treated on the scene. The two other seriously injured patients were treated on scene and once stabilised were transported by ambulance to a hospital for further treatment.